description.plain:
An American indie-progressive rock band from Nashville, Tennessee that was formed in 2006.

They have released five studio albums: Melodica (2007), Live Ride (2008), Cabaret (2012), Mountains Beaches Cities (2013), Daybreaker (2015), and Let the Record Play (2018).

songs.title: Two High

description.plain: This single is “a song about hope,” said frontman Trevor Terndrup in a statement. “Hope for understanding, hope for acceptance, and hope for our future. We were inspired by the simple and universal peace sign. It’s a gesture we would like to see more of.” The five-piece will focus on festival appearances over the coming months.
